<br>
&quot;Where is that Innoruuk damned child?&quot; a slightly sinister female voice demanded. <br>
<br>
&quot;She has to be somewhere,&quot; a male answered. <br>
<br>
&quot;We will find her,&quot; another male answered, this voice sounding even more sinister than the woman's. <br>
<br>
They left the room and Tyshalae relaxed. Perhaps they would give up their search soon and she could escape.... Then she heard soft chanting and an eerie, almost musical sound. Tysh recognized the sound of spell casting and backed even further into her corner. <br>
<br>
&quot;Hmmmm.&quot; The cupboard opened and an aged Teir'dal peered in. &quot;What a mess,&quot; he chuckled. &quot;I am not touching that.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Dantrazz, I've found your daughter,&quot; he shouted, smiling at the child he had helped raise. <br>
<br>
&quot;Papa Sol! No. Don't let them get me!&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Hush child, it is for your own good.&quot; <br>
<br>
The girl looked at her surrogate grandfather and pouted. &quot;I hate you,&quot; she mumbled. <br>
<br>
&quot;No you don't.&quot; Solaufein said, remembering similar incidents involving a very young Dantrazz. <br>
<br>
Another face joined the necromancer's. Long suffering crimson eyes met Tysh's and the handsome lips turned to a frown. &quot;She looks all sticky,&quot; Dantrazz muttered, staring at his daughter. The warrior then reached in and grabbed the squirming child. &quot;C'mon mouse, no one's going to hurt you.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;No Daddy, no! Momma's going to kill me!&quot; <br>
<br>
Dantrazz shrugged. &quot;Maybe.... Now quit wiggling.&quot; <br>
<br>
The warrior carried her up a long flight of stairs and into a small room lit with candles. It smelled of exotic incense and the air was humid. Morrigu stood within, grinning evilly at her only child. In her hand she held the object Tyshalae feared most. <br>
<br>
&quot;Hold her down love,&quot; she said softly, placing her weapon on a small table. As the strong warrior held the child immobile, the assassin pulled her clothing off. &quot;Throw her in,&quot; she whispered, indicating a cauldron of steaming liquid. <br>
<br>
&quot;No, Momma. Nooooo!&quot; The child was immersed in the warm scented water and screamed as Morrigu slid the little bar of soap over her indigo skin. <br>
<br>
&quot;You know, this wouldn't be so bad if you didn't get so dirty so fast.... Ick, your all slimy like a troll,&quot; Morrigu said as she started to clean off the layer of grime that was covering her daughter's soft indifo skin. <br>
<br>
&quot;Speaking of trolls....&quot; Dantrazz peeled a grungy little troll rag-doll off his tunic and dropped it. Tysh grabbed for it, but missed, and Quashie joined her in the bubbly water. <br>
<br>
&quot;Good idea Dan, Quashie was almost as grimy as she was.... Hold still little Feir'dal!&quot; Morrigu said, trying to grab the slippery child. <br>
<br>
Tysh turned and looked at her mother, pouting. &quot;I am not a wood elf.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;You smell like one right now Tysh,&quot; her mother said gently. <br>
<br>
Tysh settled down at this point, remembering Papa Sol's stories about the creatures of Norrath. She decided that perhaps the only thing worse than being a wood elf was being mistaken for one. She then smiled at her parents and threw her Quashie doll into the air with a giggle, letting him slash in the water. <br>
<br>
&quot;Good Tysh,&quot; Morrigu smiled. &quot;Do you want some candy?&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Yay!&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Stay still and I'll give you some.&quot; <br>
<br>
Tysh smiled at her mother, and accepted the bribe. &quot;Okies Momma.&quot; <br>
<br>
Tyshalae planned her next adventure as she let Morrigu wash her long silvery hair. She had noticed an interesting pile of muck down the street just before the dreaded bath was mentioned. If it was still there later she and Quashie would have to investigate.... <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/utyshalae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tyshalae</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Mouse</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#939393>(10/23/00 6:35:49 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/sbugelli/tyshface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A Night on the Town</span><hr size=1> &quot;...And that is the story of how Quash found true love,&quot; Morrigu said softly, gazing at her child. &quot;No more stories little mouse. It is time for you to be sleeping.&quot; Morrigu pulled the warm quilt up to Tyshalae's chin and kissed her on the forehead. &quot;Night baby.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Night Momma,&quot; the child said, yawning happily. Dantrazz and Mourn entered the darkened bedroom as Morrigu left. <br>
<br>
&quot;Bye little minx,&quot; Mourn said with a grin. &quot;See you when I get back from the Overthere.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Bye Uncle,&quot; she whispered with a smile. <br>
<br>
Dantrazz sat on the small bed and ruffled the child's silky white hair. &quot;I'm going away for a little while too Tysh. I'll bring you back something for your birthday though. What do you want?&quot; <br>
<br>
Tysh thought for a moment, then remembered the creature she had seen one of the other noble children playing with a few days earlier. &quot;A kitten!&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;I'll see what I can do. I love you Tysh,&quot;she said kissing her smooth indigo cheek. <br>
<br>
&quot;Love you too Daddy.&quot; Tyshalae hugged her father and waved as he left the room. <br>
<br>
She then closed her eyes and pretended to sleep. After a few moments her bedroom door opened again. Tysh kept her eyes closed knowing that this last visitor was shy. Her bed shifted slightly as someone very thin sat on it. A dry hand stroked her face for a moment, then receded. <br>
<br>
&quot;Sleep well my little one,&quot; Solaufein whispered. He left the room as quietly as he had entered. <br>
<br>
&quot;Night Papa Sol,&quot; she whispered to the dark. <br>
<br>
Tysh waited a few more minutes and then sat up. She swung her feet onto the floor and dug her rag-doll out from under the covers. &quot;It sounds like they've all gone to bed Quashie,&quot;she whispered, looking seriously at the small green troll.&quot;Now we can play.&quot; <br>
<br>
Tysh went to her closet and dug around for a bit. From a box for toys she pulled out a tiny outfit of leather armour she had sewn. She carefully put this on Quashie. <br>
<br>
Tysh then took out a child sized suit of leather armour that her parents had gotten Cayla, the maidservant who was helping teach Tysh things like sewing, to make for their child after it became evident that she could not be stopped from wandering out in to the forest on her own. Tysh pulled the supple armour, of a more modest cut than the leathers that adult female Teir'dal wore, on to her skinny frame and smiled at her reflection in her mirror. <br>
<br>
She then rummaged around in her red treasure sack and pulled out a dagger she had borrowed from her Momma's equipment rack earlier that day and put it on her belt. Tysh tucked Quashie in a special pocket sewn on to her tunic and grinned. <br>
<br>
The child opened her bedroom window and breathed in the scent of Neriak. The air was cool and moist and a slight mist was suspended in it, dampening sound and decreasing visibility. Tysh climbed out her window and scaled down the wall to the street. She landed like a cat. <br>
<br>
Tonight she was trying an experiment. If she failed, well she was only seven and a noble so nothing bad would really happen. If she was successful.... <br>
<br>
Several days earlier Morrigu had dragged her entire family to another noble's house for some sort of party. The males of the household had gone only reluctantly, though Tysh was excited at first. She had vague memories of several of her own birthday parties and figured that even if she was not getting any presents at least there would be sweets. <br>
<br>
Tysh had changed her mind about the affair quite swiftly. The really long bath and scratchy little dress were bad enough, but constantly being shushed by strangers, not being allowed to touch anything and the overall lack of anything good to eat made up her mind. She was about to go find her Daddy and Uncle when she noticed the guest of honour. <br>
<br>
The party was to celebrate the coming of age of a young noblewoman. The girl herself was somewhat ugly. (Papa Sol had said some of the nobles were ugly due to inbreeding, whatever that was.) Around her throat the ugly girl wore a choker unlike any piece of jewellery Tysh had ever seen. It was shinny gold, set with gems in almost every colour the child could imagine. Many of the adults at the party apparently thought it was quite a tasteless piece of jewellery, and Tysh was inclined to agree. But she thought the stones were beautiful. <br>
<br>
For the rest of the party Tyshalae wandered around the great house quietly. She looked in rooms and peered at window casings. The few adults who noticed her activities merely shooed her away, mumbling about &quot;those odd W'Rath people.&quot; Tysh did as she was told and after a while went to find her family.... <br>
<br>
The house Tysh stood before was made of large stones roughly mortared together. It was quite lovely to look at, but the architect obviously did not know any Rogues. Tyshalae climbed up the side of the building to the third floor. She edged along a convenient ledge to a window with frilly lavender curtains. <br>
<br>
&quot;We have to be very quiet now Quashie,&quot; she whispered, pulling up the window just a bit. The skinny girl slid in through the opening and landed silently on the thick carpet. Tyshalae scanned the room, finding what she sought just a few feet away. As she had hoped the girl did not wear the necklace to bed. Instead it was on a wooden stand shaped like a lady's neck and shoulders so the soft gold would keep its shape. This stand was on the girl's night table. <br>
<br>
Tysh crept across the carpet and to the table. She took the necklace off its stand and wrapped it carefully in a silk scarf that she had found on the floor. The child then stuffed her prize into a belt pouch. She moved silently to the window and slipped out again, closing it behind her. The girl had not even snored while Tysh was there. <br>
<br>
Tyshalae made her way back home quickly, avoiding all the patrolling guards and the few late night wanderers. The child climbed up to her room and changed back into her frilly nightie. She placed her treasure under her pillow. Tysh planned on prying the jewels out of the setting in the morning, and selling the gold to one of the nice trollie ladies in the Foreign Quarter. <br>
<br>
&quot;You're a good assistant thief for a trollie,&quot; Tysh whispered. She kissed Quashie's soft fabric face and smiled. Tyshalae heard footsteps in the hall and quickly feigned sleep. The door opened and someone entered her room. <br>
<br>
&quot;Silly child,&quot; the old Necromancer whispered. There was a slight clicking sound. &quot;If she doesn't start remembering to lock her window, someone's going to break in.&quot; Solaufein briefly touched her hair, not noticing the dampness from the night air that clung to it and left the room once more. <br>
<br>
Tysh suppressed a giggle, then touched her new treasure once more. She hugged Quashie tight and then fell asleep for real, a slight smile on her small lips. <br>
<br>
