<br>
As she killed a great spider for an arrogant young Necromancer she heard a commotion. There was a woman in the forest, shouting that she was to see the King and wished to have followers in her quest. Tysh's ears perked up and she made her way to the shouter. <br>
<br>
A Teir'Dal woman, dressed in black chain-mail like Tysh's Momma. Her name was Tsajin, and the King of Neriak had demanded her presence. Tysh ducked through the crowd, using her small stature to her advantage, and found herself standing beside the sinister looking woman. <br>
<br>
&quot;You've come to help me, child? Go home to your dollies,&quot; Tsajin sneered. Tysh sneered right back of course. <br>
<br>
The crowd moved to the Foreign Quarter and the King appeared. He was tall and dressed in armour like her Daddy's, save that it was dark, not bight and shinny. The High Cleric of Innoruuk stood beside the King. These three great figures argued among themselves. A smelly old book of some sort was to be found in Lavastorm and the dark lady would be rewarded if she found it. <br>
<br>
Tsajin led the grown ups out in to the Forest, leaving Tysh alone with the King. She fidgeted for a moment and then smiled at the man, hoping he would give her some candy. &quot;Ummm, hi your Majesty.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Greetings child. Are you loyal to your King?&quot; he asked. <br>
<br>
Tysh hesitated. She had no reason not to be loyal she supposed. &quot;Uhuh.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Then why did you not go with the others?&quot; <br>
<br>
Tysh stared up at the man and frowned. &quot;I'm too little.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Nay, follow along, make sure that Tsajin woman does her duty. I do not trust her.&quot; <br>
<br>
Tysh shrugged. &quot;Ok.&quot; She wandered out in to the forest and hid, not wanting to risk the ire of the King or her family. Tysh knew if her Momma ever found out she was in Lavastorm before she turned sixteen her Momma would have Papa Sol skin her alive or something equally unpleasant. But she had also learned to not outright disobey people in front of their noses. It was fine to do whatever you wanted behind their backs, Mommas and Kings included. <br>
<br>
After a time Tsajin and her hoard returned. Tysh quickly joined the group and followed to Third Gate. The King and his Rogue met. She refused to give up the book, demanding a tenth of the city's treasure first. The King became angered and killed her, taking the book from her dead hands. Tysh suppressed a shriek during al this, quietly wiping a bit of the dead woman's blood from her face. She wanted to go home, but was swept up in the crowd once again. They went deeper in to the Noble Quarter, stopping at the river. The King, his Cleric and a young Prophet swam to the conical island with in the river warning all others to stay back. Two young women waited on the island, a Dark Elf and a High Elf. <br>
<br>
The Dark Elf came up to the King, face etched with an expression of pure ecstasy. He drove a sword through her and the crowd cheered. Tysh felt her stomach churn. <br>
<br>
Next the king turned to the light dweller. Tysh was very unsure about her feelings towards the High Elves. She supposed she did not mind the Wood Elves, even if they did smell funny. They gave her candy and made her run very fast. High Elves were always rude to the child though. But she could not help feeling bad for this young elf. She was barely older than Tysh and screaming to be rescued. Tyshalae watched as one caster tried to save the girl, but she was slain instantly by the High Cleric. The King then killed the girl and the crowd cheered again. <br>
<br>
Then they became silent. A disgusting smelling wind started blowing and the air shimmered.... At the top of the island a creature had appeared. Tall and ugly, covered in warts and with horns on its head. His limbs were twisted and his eyes burned with evil. Shouts of &quot;Innoruuk bless us&quot; and &quot;Hail the Avatar of Hate&quot; could be heard. <br>
<br>
So this is our God, Tysh thought, a crippled old monster with body odour. She shrugged, Yathrin and the others could worship this beast, Tysh preferred to depend on her self. <br>
<br>
The God's avatar started screaming and the young Prophet listened intently, hoping to translate its words for the King. Tysh fidgeted, this was beginning to bore her. Then some fool in the crowd cast a spell on the Avatar. It screamed even louder and lunged into the crowd. Tysh could have reached her hand out and touched its disgusting blue-green skin. Instead she screamed and started running.... Tysh slowed a block from her home and calmly entered her home. Papa Sol was waiting by the door. <br>
<br>
&quot;Are the half wits enjoying their show?&quot; he asked grinning. Tysh nodded, frowning. <br>
<br>
&quot;I trust you are not converting little one?&quot; he asked gently. <br>
<br>
&quot;No way,&quot; Tysh said. &quot;He smelled bad.... And the way everyone was acting, that is what I hate about our people.... I think I want that bath now Papa Sol. I feel icky.&quot; <br>
<br>
The old Necromancer smiled gently at the child. &quot;Those people make me feel the same way child.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Why is Auntie Yathy different from them? She's a priestess of that creature,&quot; Tysh asked, holding the old Dark Elf's hand. <br>
<br>
&quot;Yathrin is just different child. Cherish those differences, do not question them. Come, your mother will be pleased to see you requesting a bath for once.&quot; <br>
<br>
Tysh grinned. &quot;This will be the only time it happens, believe me Papa Sol.&quot; Both laughed and like all the bad things that had ever happened to the small girl, the fear she had felt earlier was quickly forgotten. <br>
<br>
