<br>
He picked up a cheap book full of drawings of various types of naked female elves and started grinning. Tysh then turned her attention to the prisoner in the room's tiny cell. <br>
<br>
Lanneth Shadowborn, Half-elf ranger, was asleep, leaning against the bars of his barren cell. Tysh had been sneaking here and watching him for almost a week, since the day she and Auntie Mystie had seen him dragged through Neriak in chains. The wounded mess of his eye was looking better on this day, though there was a new gash on one fair cheek. Tysh felt some pity for him. He was only a little older than she was and had been caught doing something braver than she would ever do. <br>
<br>
The guard started snoring and Tysh grinned. She pulled her troll rag-doll from his special pouch. &quot;Well Quashie, guess we're gonna have to wake him.&quot; She grasped Quashie around his plump cloth body and swiftly thwacked the sleeper in the head. The toy's small metal helmet connected with skull and the Ranger awoke with a start. <br>
<br>
&quot;Who?&quot; he mumbled, staring at the young Dark Elf. <br>
<br>
&quot;Who the Hell were you expecting? Tuna Air?&quot; She had heard the curse word in the Foreign Quarter and was trying to use it as much as possible, away from the ears of family and guild of course. <br>
<br>
&quot;No, I guess not,&quot; he whispered. &quot;Well, who are you?&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Not important. I'm a friend of some of your friends Lanneth. They're worried ‘bout you.&quot; He nodded. &quot;I've been keepin' an eye on ya for the last week.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;That so?&quot; he whispered, probably amazed that a child so young could make her way into the bowels of the prison on her own. <br>
<br>
&quot;You can trust me Pinky,&quot; Tysh said, pointing to the guild pin on her chain mail tunic. &quot;Evoluxa does.&quot; She pulled a small bag out of her back pack. &quot;Food, water and bandages. Looks like you could use ‘em.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;I could. And what do I tell the guards if they find it?&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;I dunno, say a mouse dragged it in. They'll beat the hell outta you if they find it no matter what you say.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Well, thank you Mouse.&quot; <br>
<br>
Tysh grinned. &quot;If you got a message you want to send anyone I'll be back tomorrow.&quot; She heard a nearby door open. &quot;I gotta go. I'd wish ya luck, but you're a Pinky and, well....&quot; She shrugged and slipped into the shadows by the door. <br>
<br>
A guard walked in, stared at Lanneth for a moment, a cruel smile on his indigo face, then moved to wake his friend. Tysh slipped out the briefly opened door. She then spent the better part of an hour working her way out of the prison. <br>
<br>
&quot;Well Quashie,&quot; she said, ginning at the stuffed troll, breathing in the damp air of Neriak. &quot;Guess we're gonna have to go shoppin' before we go back to Oasis.&quot; Tysh stared quizzically at the toy for a moment, as if listening. &quot;Yeah, I know I'm gettin' soft...all that peace an' love from the guild I guess. Let's go kill some halflings first, before we get to the lizzies. That'll straighten me up. I promised Daddy I wouldn't eat any of the guild and its been gettin' to me.&quot; <br>
<br>
She grinned, thinking of nothing more than fresh meat and started humming a happy little tune, imagining that Quashie was singing along with her, in a pleasantly deep trollish voice. <br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/utyshalae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tyshalae</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 10/23/00 6:38:46 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/utyshalae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tyshalae</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Mouse</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#939393>(10/23/00 6:39:43 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/sbugelli/tyshface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Urchin and the Mouse</span><hr size=1> Morrigu opened her daughter's bedroom door and smiled. There was no sign of her child in the narrow bed. On one half slept Bane, the giant kitten, and on the other half laid a variety of stuffed animals. The only thing that betrayed her child's existence was a stray lock of silvery hair. <br>
<br>
&quot;Caught you little Mouse,&quot; she said, smiling. <br>
<br>
Tyshalae sprung up, sending toys and one very big kitty flying. The child grinned and giggled, waving her rag-doll around happily. &quot;Mornin' Momma!&quot; <br>
<br>
Morrigu sat on the edge of her child's bed and ruffled her long silky hair. &quot;Papa Sol is busy this morning, so no lessons ‘till this afternoon. Do you want to go outside and play Tysh?&quot; <br>
<br>
Tysh grinned. &quot;Yay!&quot; She loved her lessons with Papa Sol, but there was something she needed hunt for in the city. <br>
<br>
Tysh pulled on regular play cloths, leather leggings and a big cotton tunic, instead of her armour, then followed her mother to the kitchen. Morrigu gave her a bottle of milk and several warm muffins. &quot;You be good.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Of course Momma,&quot; Tysh said, trying to look innocent. <br>
<br>
&quot;Right.&quot; Morrigu bent down and kissed her daughter on the forehead. <br>
<br>
&quot;Quashie said he wants a kiss too, Momma,&quot; the child giggled, holding the somewhat grungy toy in Morrigu's face. <br>
<br>
She looked at Tysh and grinned, then planted her sensuous lips on the rag-doll's bald green head. Morrigu watched as they ran out of the house and smiled, then set about her morning tasks. <br>
<br>
Tysh sat on the curb for a few moments and discussed today's plan with Quashie between bits of muffin. They were going to sneak into House D'Noir today. Rumour around the Foreign Quarter said that Matron Ferall had taken in an urchin and was nursing him back to health. Tysh knew the Matron was odd, but this merited further investigation. Everyone knew the proper thing to do with urchins was steam them lightly and eat them with butter sauce. <br>
<br>
They walked down the narrow street, then sneaked into an alley way. &quot;Be quiet now, Quashie,&quot; Tysh warned, tucking the toy into his special pouch. &quot;The skelly guards won't see us, but they can hear us.&quot; The child then sneaked through the fence, past the undead guards who remained after the second disappearance of their master and up the stone wall. <br>
<br>
Tysh crept along the narrow ledge and into an open window. She landed softly in a dark hallway. A door opened and the Matron and a serving girl left, closing the door softly behind them. <br>
<br>
&quot;That must be the urchin's room,&quot; Tysh whispered for Quashie's benefit, as he could not see out of the belt pouch. The child crept into the room and regarded its occupant. A small, bruised Tier'dal boy laid in a large bed, thick blankets tucked all around him. His eyes were closed, but he sensed her presence somehow. <br>
<br>
&quot;Who's there?&quot; he whispered in a soft, hoarse voice. <br>
<br>
Tysh moved to the bed and looked at him, smiling. &quot;I'm Tysh, who the Hell are you?&quot; <br>
<br>
The boy managed a grin. &quot;I'm Elil.... Why are you here?&quot; <br>
<br>
She shrugged. &quot;I'm lookin' for an urchin. You seen it? ‘Bout the size of an apple, kinda prickly, lives underwater?&quot; <br>
<br>
For some reason the boy, wounded and half starved as he was, started laughing. <br>
<br>
&quot;What?&quot; Tysh stared at him, utterly confused. &quot;What the Hell is so funny?&quot; <br>
<br>
************ <br>
<br>
Tysh wandered into Papa Sol's study several hours later, Quashie swinging at her side, both humming a happy little song. <br>
<br>
&quot;I trust you had an enjoyable morning, little one?&quot; the old Necromancer said, looking up from his book. <br>
<br>
&quot;I did!&quot; she exclaimed, climbing on to a stool by her Papa's desk. &quot;I made a friend! Or at least I think I did. He didn't call me un-natch-eral or nothin' like the other kids do.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;That is pleasant indeed Tyshalae.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah, but I never found Matron Ferall's sea urchin,&quot; she mumbled. <br>
<br>
The Necromancer looked at the child, puzzled. He had quite a bit of experience with young W'Raths and knew sometimes it was better for his sanity if he just did not ask. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/utyshalae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tyshalae</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Mouse</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#939393>(10/23/00 6:41:09 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/sbugelli/tyshface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Aftermath</span><hr size=1> Tyshalae pulled the vile smelling gland from a fire drake and carefully slid it into a heavy glass jar, which she then placed into her sturdy backpack. She then pulled her well-loved troll doll from his special pouch and grinned at him. <br>
<br>
&quot;Time to go home Quashie.&quot; She drank back a wolfie feets potion and started running. The journey from Lavastorm to Third Gate was a long one, but fast feets and a trollie's pleasant company made it go quite quickly. <br>
<br>
As she ran she heard distressing rumours of people just vanishing from the face of Norrath. Tysh shrugged and kept running. House W&quot;Rath was stronger than such things... besides her whole crazy extended family was meeting at her home that afternoon, for they had not seen each other for a while. Tysh decided to run faster, suddenly worries that they might think she was gone too. <br>
<br>
She rushed up to the door and burst in, grinning. &quot;I's here!&quot; She was meet only by Bane, making the heart wenching whine of a sad feline. <br>
<br>
&quot;Hello?&quot; Tysh shouted, suddenly scared. The child searched her home and found no one, no sign that the preparations for the party had even started. Even the servants were gone. <br>
<br>
She sat on her bed for a while and cried. Her whole family, Momma, Daddy, Papa Sol, Uncle Mourn, Auntie Mystie, Yathy and Oifie, seemed to be gone.... Tysh cried and cried, then started thinking. <br>
<br>
Her parents always stressed that she was not safe without them Neriak, for her House had many enemies. Tysh grabbed her red velvet sack and started packing her most treasured belongings in it. She found the leash and harness that she had crafted for Bane so he could go outside and play. She secured her sack to her back, drank a wolfie feets potion, fed another to her cat and started running. <br>
<br>
The girl and her pet ran for many miles, all the way to Oasis. They stopped at the docks. Tysh peered at a kindly looking dwarf and tried to smile. <br>
<br>
